text:
Queensland to shine with Pride of the West Festival
Make your way to Quilpie’s Bulloo Park in Queensland for the Quilpie Diggers Race Club annual Station Challenge Pride of the West Race Day.
The weekend kicks off on Friday (Sept 25) with the two handed cutting and live music and bar until late.
On Saturday (Sept 26) head track side for a great day of country racing. All races feature station horses and local riders!
The title “The Pride of the West” is awarded to the horse which wins the final race after four heats.
Proterra Group and APV Contracting Fashions are back on the field again this Pride of the West Festival and with six categories to be contended the competition is sure to be fierce.
Fashion conscious boys and girls aged 11 years and under the Yearlings category is for you. The judges will be looking for kids whose outfits are fun, fashionable and original while still being raceday and age appropriate. For girls headwear is not compulsory but would be an advantage; for boys jackets, ties/bow ties and hats are not compulsory but would also be an advantage
